A Conflict of interest between her thriving television career with Multichoice has cost radio and television personalityZama Ngcobo her job as part of Ukhozi FM s Vuka Mzansi Breakfast show.Ngcobo tweeted what looked like correspondence between herself and her bosses earlier in the week, before the station came out to confirm the news yesterday. We have considered the information and have concluded that it would be a conflict of interest in the event that your DStv agreement were to coexist in parallel to our contract, reads part of the letter she received from the station.Ukhozi FM, the country s biggest radio with 7.7 million listeners, confirmed her exit.